Vintage illustration of a broken mechanical pocket watch with its gears and springs spilling out onto an antique wooden desk, surrounded by scattered paper documents with technical diagrams and blueprints. The watch face shows conflicting time zones. In the background, three different old-fashioned typewriters sit at odd angles, each appearing to be from a different era and incompatible with one another. Muted sepia tones with pops of aged brass and copper colors. The scene suggests elegant machinery that refuses to work together, with visible frustration implied through the chaotic arrangement of precisely engineered but mismatched components. Soft directional lighting from an unseen window creates dramatic shadows across the cluttered workspace.
